history.content: 61C does not always expand to accommodate everyone - Nick's policy for the past few semesters has been to only expand when we get the matching budget to support students, and we have not been getting the budget we need to accommodate everyone for a few semesters now (@16046). I would still stay on the waitlist for a bit just to see what the drop rate is like, but I would also have a backup ready just in case.

I know CS61C is historically a class that expands to accommodate everyone; however, it seems in fall 2021 this class was underfunded/had budget constraints? Will the class still expand for the spring at this point? I am currently at position #76 on the waitlist. Thanks!
history.subject: Will CS61C expand more this semester?
